  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Caroline Weston went to visit &quot;Brother Mark&apos;s&quot; and developed a high fever there. She met a woman who helped George Thompson escape from a mob in Lowell. Caroline wrote: &quot;I invited their worship by telling all the tough stories I could think of. Nothing sews them up like the horrors...&quot; H.B. Stanton lectured well and brought good news. Caroline went to a meeting in Waltham. She describes what she did on every other day of the week. She mentions a peace meeting at the Ammidons.</subfield>
  </datafield>
